body: Excuse me, I meet the same question, so how do you solve it??

> Thank you for your code. Your code is excellent but difficult for me use. In short, I do not know how to use the voxelmorph code yet, although I tried to many run times (> 4 times) . Please help me some questions.
> 
> 1. I tried to do Training step:
>    ./scripts/tf/train.py /path/to/training/data --model-dir /path/to/models/output --gpu 0
>    And, I typed like this but had the error --img-list. How do I fill this request? Thank you.
>    ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37217354/135755937-3b50392f-0124-4434-965c-61532a346da3.png)
> 2. I do not know about the data folder. I mean I do not know, how to load the .npz file in this folder when I train.
>    For example, which .npz file is Moving image or Fixed image, respectively?
>    ![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/37217354/135755824-29539a50-53a4-43e2-90b8-a093ec59c331.png)
> 
> Thank you very much.

Excuse me, I meet the same question, so how do you solve it??

Our apologies I think we changed the default way to feed in data recently.
the IMG_LIST should be a text file, where each line is a file in your dataset.

For example, you can download the brain data from 
https://github.com/adalca/medical-datasets/blob/master/neurite-oasis.md
then your IMG_LIST can be a list of the files you want to train with from that dataset, like:

```
/path/to/neurite/oasis/OASIS_OAS1_0001_MR1/slice_norm.nii.gz
/path/to/neurite/oasis/OASIS_OAS1_0002_MR1/slice_norm.nii.gz
...
```

@ahoopes is this right?

Yes, this is correct. Sorry for the confusion. I've updated the README with new instructions.

Basically, you'll need some file that lists the unique image filenames in your training dataset. This doesn't necessarily have to include the full paths though, as you can use the `--img-prefix` and `--img-suffix` flags to add information. For example, in the OASIS dataset that Adrian linked, you can use `subjects.txt` (included in the dataset) as your file list, and use `--img-prefix /path/to/downloaded/dataset/` and `--img-suffix /norm.nii.gz` to specify where the data is stored and which image file to use from the subject folders.

From the updated README:

>  For a given image list file `/images/list.txt` and output directory `/models/output`, the following script will train an image-to-image registration network (described in MICCAI 2018 by default) with an unsupervised loss. Model weights will be saved to a path specified by the `--model-dir` flag.
> 
> ```
> ./scripts/tf/train.py --img-list /images/list.txt --model-dir /models/output --gpu 0
> ```
> 
> The `--img-prefix` and `--img-suffix` flags can be used to provide a consistent prefix or suffix to each path specified in the image list.

issue.title: Training scripts call example
issue.body:
It seems the description is not updated 

     ./scripts/tf/train.py /path/to/training/data --model-dir /path/to/models/output --gpu 0

The [script](https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph/blob/dev/scripts/torch/train.py) requires [img-list](https://github.com/voxelmorph/voxelmorph/blob/229a74781331c289b59efeacc79106278cc63eaa/scripts/torch/train.py#L52)

     parser.add_argument('--img-list', required=True, help='line-seperated list of training files')) 

which is not mentioned in the example script call above.

It would be nice to add an example for -img-list.
